# Database Design

## Prefer Database Enforcement

Instead of:

```
Validate → Insert
```

Prefer:

```
Constraint → Insert → Catch Exception
```

## Always Prefer

- Foreign keys for referential integrity
- CHECK constraints for invariants
- EXCLUDE constraints for overlap/conflict rules
- Partial indexes for filtered hot paths
- Transactions for multi-step atomic operations

## Before Writing SQL, Ask

```
Can Postgres enforce this?
Can a CHECK constraint solve this?
Can an EXCLUDE constraint solve this?
Can a partial index solve this?
Should this be transactional?
```

## Examples

```sql
-- ❌ BAD — overlap checked only in application code
-- App: SELECT ... WHERE start < $end AND end > $start

-- ✅ GOOD — EXCLUDE constraint enforces no overlap at DB level
ALTER TABLE bookings ADD CONSTRAINT no_overlap
  EXCLUDE USING gist (asset_id WITH =, tsrange(start_at, end_at) WITH &&);
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — two separate operations, no atomicity
await prisma.allocation.delete({ where: { id } });
await prisma.asset.update({ where: { id }, data: { status: 'available' } });

// ✅ GOOD — single transaction
await prisma.$transaction([
  prisma.allocation.delete({ where: { id } }),
  prisma.asset.update({ where: { id }, data: { status: 'available' } }),
]);
```
